<TITLE> Tokyo evacuates 16,000 to defuse wartime bomb </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TOKYO, Sun May 18, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Tokyo ordered about 16,000 residents to evacuate on Sunday while a bomb squad disposed of an unexploded bomb believed to have fallen during World War II in western Tokyo, Kyodo News said. Ground Self-Defense Force members removed the fuse of the dud in a two-hour operation earlier in the day, and the Chofu city government declared the area safe and called off the alert, Kyodo said. The local government ordered people living in a radius of about 500 meters around the scene to evacuate and suspended part of train services in the area, it said. The 180-centimeter-long, 600-centimeter-diameter dud, believed to be a 1-ton bomb which was apparently dropped from a U.S. B-29 bomber which crashed in April 1945, was found in March this year, Kyodo s
